{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "manifest_id": "conditional-group-exists-boundary",
  "spec_refs": [
    "docs/benchmarks/plan.md",
    "docs/spec/drop-in-re-compatibility.md"
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Conditional group-exists boundary workloads keep one optional capture, one conditional site, and tiny haystacks so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded two-arm conditional slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(b)?c(?(1)d|e)` and `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)d|e)` compile/search/fullmatch paths directly, the bounded nested two-arm `a(b)?c(?(1)(?(1)d|e)|f)` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)(?(word)d|e)|f)` module-search and Pattern.fullmatch probes, one bounded quantified `{2}` Pattern.fullmatch companion for each numbered and named spelling, and the bounded alternation-heavy `a(b)?c(?(1)(de|df)|(eg|eh))` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)(de|df)|(eg|eh))` module-search and Pattern.fullmatch probes, while broader replacement-conditioned, repeated alternation-heavy, deeper nested, and branch-local-backreference conditional shapes stay explicit gaps in their own manifests instead of being silently omitted here."
  ],
  "defaults": {
    "warmup_iterations": 2,
    "sample_iterations": 5,
    "timed_samples": 7
  },
